public enum EventType

An enum for the different types of events that can cause a hook to run.

Author:
cvh

Enum Constant Detail

preConnect

public static final EventType preConnect
The pre-connect event happens before a connection is leased.

See Also:
Settings.addPreConnectHook(Hook)

postConnect

public static final EventType postConnect
The post-connect event happens after a connection has been leased or the lease attempt has decidedly failed with an SQLException, but before that connection is returned, or the exception thrown, to the caller of NanoPoolDataSource.getConnection().

See Also:
Settings.addPostConnectHook(Hook)

preRelease

public static final EventType preRelease
The pre-release event happens before a leased connection returns to the pool. Note that throwing from a pre-release hook does not abrupt or abort any flow inside of NanoPool - it is a safe thing to do from the perspective of NanoPool itself.

See Also:
Settings.addPreReleaseHook(Hook)

postRelease

public static final EventType postRelease
The post-release event happens after a connection lease has returned to the pool. Be mindful of race conditions here, because the connection might have been re-leased at this point, or the physical connection might have been closed.

See Also:
Settings.addPostReleaseHook(Hook)

invalidation

public static final EventType invalidation
The invalidation event happens after a physical connection has been closed but before any post-release event. If an SQLException is thrown by the JDBC driver while closing the physical connection, then that exception will be passed to the hooks as a parameter.

See Also:
Settings.addConnectionInvalidationHook(Hook)
